record_data.record_title: FMES FERC Electric Tariff Second Revised Volume No. 1
record_data.record_plain_text: FREEPORT-MCMORAN COPPER & GOLD ENERGY SERVICES, LLC FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF VOLUME NO. 1 1. Availability: Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Energy Services, LLC ("Seller") makes electric energy and capacity available for resale under this FERC Electric Tariff Volume No. 1 ("Rate Schedule") to any wholesale purchaser with whom Seller has contracted ("Eligible Purchaser"). 2. Applicability: This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of energy or capacity by Seller not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Seller. 3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the Eligible Purchaser and Seller. 4. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Rate Schedule or otherwise restricts or limits Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Rate Schedule. 5. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Seller does not have any limitations on its market-based rate authority, except as may otherwise be provided in this Rate Schedule. Seller has obtained waivers of: Subpart B and C of Part 35 regarding the filing of tariffs, with the exception of sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, regarding accounts; Part 101, regarding a uniform system of accounts; and Part 141, regarding statements and reports. Seller has blanket approval under Part 34 of the Commission's regulations of future issuances of securities and assumptions of liabilities, subject to the objection of an interested party. Green Power Partners I, LLC, 88 FERC 61,005 (1999). The Commission granted Seller a waiver of sections 35.39(b) and 35.44(a) of the Commission's regulations to engage in wholesale power sales between Seller and its affiliates, Ajo Improvement Company and Morenci Water & Electric Company, provided that rates for such wholesale sales will be based solely on Seller's costs. 6. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between Eligible Purchaser and Seller. 7. Effective Date: This Rate Schedule is effective as of the date specified by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. 8. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 1 seller as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a) in the Northeast, Southeast, Central, SPP, Southwest and Northwest regions.
